otism. Today, as cultural institutions reappraise their relevance, Made in Newark explores precedents for contemporary debates over the ways the library and museum engage communities, define heritage in a multicultural era, and add value to the economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aArts and crafts movementzUnited States. 0aLibrarianszNew JerseyzNewarkvBiography. 0aLibraries and community. 0aMuseum directorszNew JerseyzNewarkvBiography. 0aMuseums and community. 0aMuseumszNew JerseyzNewarkxHistory. 0aPublic librarieszNew JerseyzNewarkxHistory. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831106886100 cprintz978081354769540uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081354992740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813549927423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813549927/original  a978-3-11-068861-0  Rutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK